<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870302-0174 </DOCNO><HL> Owens-Corning Sells Unit</HL><DD> 03/02/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> OCFTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> TOLEDO, Ohio  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Owens-Corning Fiberglas Corp. said it completed the previously announced sale of its contracting subsidiary, Performance Contracting Inc., to a new company formed by managers of the subsidiary.    Terms weren't disclosed, but Owens-Corning said Performance Contracting's 1986 revenue was about $138 million.    Owens-Corning makes glass fiber insulation and construction products. Its 1986 sales totaled $3.64 billion. </TEXT></DOC>